# Main.elm — EARLY

TEA bootstrap for the standalone LynRummy Elm game. Replaces
TS's `plugin.ts` factory. First milestone renders only the
opening board; no Msgs, no interaction.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Entry point scaffolding; will grow as we
  wire interaction.
- **Source:** new Elm file (no 1:1 TS source). Conceptually
  replaces `plugin.ts`'s role of bootstrapping the game into
  the host.

## Scope of the first milestone

- Model: `{ board : List CardStack }`, initialized from
  `LynRummy.Dealer.initialBoard`.
- Msg: placeholder variant (`NoOp`) — nothing dispatches yet.
- update: no-op.
- view: `LynRummy.View.viewBoardHeading` + `viewBoard model.board`.
- main: `Browser.element` with empty subscriptions.

## Deferred (grows as the port continues)

- Hand zone, action buttons, turn chrome.
- Drag/drop (Msgs for DragStart / DragMove / DragEnd).
- Turn orchestration (PlayerTurn integration).
- Referee validation + any wire plumbing (V2).

## Pointers

- `index.html` in same dir hosts the `elm.js` build.
- Serve via `python3 -m http.server 8788` from
  `games/lynrummy/elm-port-docs/`.
